and most people are about to do the same thing:
apply → gets no response →repeat.

No feedback. No clue what went wrong.

That’s exactly why Resume Sutra exists.

What it helps you with:

Tells you what’s actually wrong in your resume

Fixes weak lines like “worked on…” →makes them impactful

Matches your resume with a Job Description (JD)

🧠 Pucho: turns your resume into real interview questions

Lets you practice answers before the actual interview. In short, it&#39;s shortlist engine :)

The truth is:
Most resumes aren’t bad….they are just unclear.

And interviews? Even tougher if you can’t explain your own work.

Try it once: https://resume-sutra-7i6v.vercel.app/
(people have generated 53 resume till now)

If you’re applying this season, this might actually help more than you expect.

And yeah, send this to your friends too cuz everyone’s silently struggling with the same thing even me too.‬"><div class="x1c4vz4f x3nfvp2 xuce83p x1bft6iq x1i7k8ik xq9mrsl x6s0dn4"><div class="x78zum5"><span dir="auto" aria-label="Maybe Swayam Gupta" class="x1rg5ohu _ao3e" style="min-height: 0px;">~ Swayam Gupta</span></div></div><span>:&nbsp;</span><span dir="ltr" class="x1iyjqo2 x6ikm8r x10wlt62 x1n2onr6 xlyipyv xuxw1ft x1rg5ohu _ao3e" style="min-height: 0px;">Internship &amp; Placement Season is around the corner…

